    <p>
        Two molecular statements are <term>logically equivalent</term> if they have the exact same truth values.
        To check logical equivalence, make a truth table for each and check whether the columns corresponding to the truth values of the statements are identical.
    </p>
    
    <exploration>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Are the following pairs of statements logically equivalent? Justify.
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li><m>P\land (Q\lor R)</m> and <m>(P\land Q) \lor (P\land R)</m></li>
                <li><m>P\lor (Q\land R)</m> and <m>(P\lor Q) \land (P\lor R)</m></li>
                <li><m>\neg(P\land Q)</m> and <m>(\neg P) \lor (\neg Q)</m></li>
                <li><m>\neg(P\lor Q)</m> and <m>(\neg P) \land (\neg Q)</m></li>
                <li><m>P\imp Q</m> and <m>(\neg P) \lor Q</m></li>
                <li><m>\neg (P\imp Q)</m> and <m>P\land (\neg Q)</m></li>
                <li><m>P\imp (Q\lor R)</m> and <m>(P\land (\neg Q))\imp R</m></li>
                <li><m>P\imp Q</m> and <m>Q\imp P</m></li>
                <li><m>P\imp Q</m> and <m>(\neg Q)\imp (\neg P)</m></li>
